
[1]effloresce

   EFFLORESCE, v.t. efflores'. [L. effloresco, from floresco, floreo, to
   blossom, flos, a flower. See Flower.

   1. In chimistry, to form a mealy powder on the surface; to become
   pulverulent or dusty on the surface. Substances effloresce by losing
   their water of crystallization.

   Those salts whose crystals effloresce, belong to the class which is
   most soluble, and crystalize by cooling.

   2. To form saline vegetation on the surface; or rather to shoot out
   minute spicular crystals; as the efflorescence of salts on plaster.
